ias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/11\/30\/ibn-masud-fear-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":32015,"position":0},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Taqwa: Sinful to show anger when told to fear Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Wahb reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIt is enough sin for a man to get angry when he is told to fear Allah.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r 8588 Grade: Rijal al-Sahih (narrators are reliable) according to Al-Haythami \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0628\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22480,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/04\/07\/suppress-rage-save-adhab\/","url_meta":{"origin":32015,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Anger: Suppressing anger saves from punishment","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 7, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever restricts his tongue, Allah will cover his faults. Whoever restrains his anger, Allah will restrain his punishment on the Day of Resurrection. Whoever apologizes to Allah, Allah Almighty will accept his apology.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32017,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/14\/saying-benefit-hereafter-anger\/","url_meta":{"origin":32015,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Anger: Teach me a saying to benefit me in the Hereafter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 14, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Ahnaf ibn Qays reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, give me a word that will benefit me, but keep it short so I can understand it.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not be angry.\u201d The man repeated the question, and the\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32013,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/13\/anger-rise-every-evil\/","url_meta":{"origin":32015,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Rage: Anger gives rise to every evil","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Humayd reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, instruct me.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not be angry.\u201d The man said, \u201cI reflected upon what the Prophet said, and it occurred to me that anger gives rise to every evil.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 23171\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38216,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/09\/08\/umar-control-anger-whims\/","url_meta":{"origin":32015,"position":4},"title":"Umar on Taqwa: Fear Allah, control anger and desires","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 8, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Abdullah al-Khurasani reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhoever fears Allah does not vent his anger, and whoever is mindful of Allah does not do whatever he desires.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 98 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u0631\u0627\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u0636\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42008,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/07\/21\/manhood-slow-to-anger\/","url_meta":{"origin":32015,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Manliness: Slow to be angry, fast to reconcile","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 21, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, the best of men are slow to anger and quick to be appeased, and the most evil of men are quick to anger and slow to be appeased.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 11143 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"